        "score": 0.5171443,
        "text": "The document discusses pricing and settlement methods for capacity resources in Zone J, focusing on resource adequacy and transmission security. It outlines a scenario where the incremental price for resource adequacy is $5.60 per kW-month, and for transmission security, it's $7.50 per kW-month. Most Zone J resources receive the full clearing price of $19 per kW-month, while others receive $11.50 based on resource adequacy.\n\nThree hypothetical resources are illustrated:\n\n1. SCRs receive $11.50 per kW-month.\n2. A 1000 MW generator is paid for 720 MW at $19 per kW-month and 230 MW at $11.50.\n3. An 800 MW offshore wind unit is paid for 200 MW at $11.50 and 80 MW at $7.50.\n\nThe document recommends a two-part pricing method to separate payments for resource adequacy and transmission security, aiming to improve investment incentives and reduce overpayments.\n\nAdditionally, it critiques the NYISO's deliverability test methodology, noting its misalignment with resource adequacy analyses and its potential impact on estimating resources' deliverability as renewables and storage grow.",
