        "score": 0.5128374,
        "text": "The document discusses the management of the 115 kV Gardenville-to-Dunkirk lines by the NYISO, which involves taking certain lines out of service to reduce load on the PJM-NYISO interface. In 2015, specific lines were taken out for significant hours to manage congestion, but exporters were not charged for the associated congestion costs. The document suggests modeling these constraints in scheduling and pricing software to better manage congestion and reduce uplift costs.\n\nAdditionally, it covers Guarantee Payment Uplift Charges, explaining that NYISO recovers payments to market participants through these charges. Minimizing uplift charges is crucial as they are hard to hedge and lack transparency, affecting market signals. The document includes a reference to figures showing uplift charges for various reliability categories in 2014 and 2015.",
